  "text": "## LLVM Pass Manager Registration and Execution Chain\n\n### Overview\nLLVM uses a sophisticated pass infrastructure with two systems: the Legacy PassManager and the New PassManager. The New PassManager uses modern C++ template-based design with concept-based polymorphism.\n\n### PassManager Template (llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManager.h)\nThe core PassManager is a template class that manages sequences of passes over IR units (Modules, Functions, Loops, etc.). Key features:\n- Template parameters: IRUnitT (e.g., Module, Function), AnalysisManagerT, ExtraArgTs\n- Specializations for ModulePassManager and FunctionPassManager (lines 238, 247)\n- Uses `addPass()` template method (lines 193-214) which uses concept-based polymorphism\n- Each pass is wrapped in a PassModel that implements the PassConcept interface\n- Executes passes via the `run()` method which:\n  1. Iterates through stored passes\n  2. Calls each pass's run() method with the IR unit\n  3. Updates analysis results based on PreservedAnalyses returned by each pass\n\n### PassRegistry (llvm/include/llvm/PassRegistry.h and llvm/lib/IR/PassRegistry.cpp)\nProvides global registration and lookup for passes:\n- PassRegistry::getPassRegistry() returns the singleton global registry (PassRegistry.cpp:23-26)\n- Stores PassInfo objects in two maps: by type ID and by string name (PassRegistry.h:42-46)\n- registerPass() method adds PassInfo to both maps (PassRegistry.cpp:48-62)\n- Used by legacy PassManager for dependency resolution\n- Thread-unsafe by design - each thread needs its own registry\n\n### PassInfo (llvm/include/llvm/PassInfo.h)\nMetadata class for passes containing:\n- Pass name and command-line argument (lines 34-35)\n- Pass ID pointer (type identifier) (line 36)\n- Function pointer to pass constructor (line 39)\n- Flags indicating analysis/CFG-only status (lines 37-38)\n- Used primarily by legacy passes but referenced in modern infrastructure\n\n### PassBuilder (llvm/include/llvm/Passes/PassBuilder.h)\nThe main class for constructing standard optimization pipelines:\n- Holds TargetMachine, PipelineTuningOptions, PGOOptions\n- Core pipeline building methods:\n  - buildPerModuleDefaultPipeline() - per-module default pipeline for O1/O2/O3 (line 258)\n  - buildModuleSimplificationPipeline() - canonicalization and simplification passes (line 223)\n  - buildModuleOptimizationPipeline() - speed optimization passes (line 249)\n  - buildInlinerPipeline() - inlining passes (line 228)\n  - buildFunctionSimplificationPipeline() - per-function simplification (line 205)\n\n### Standard Optimization Pipeline (llvm/lib/Passes/PassBuilderPipelines.cpp)\nImplements the actual pipeline construction for O2/O3 optimization levels:\n\n**buildPerModuleDefaultPipeline (lines 1715-1761)**:\n1. Returns O0 pipeline for O0 level\n2. Adds memory profiling cleanup if non-LTO\n3. Adds annotation to metadata conversion\n4. Adds force function attributes\n5. Calls buildModuleSimplificationPipeline (line 1746)\n6. Calls buildModuleOptimizationPipeline (line 1749)\n7. Adds LTO pre-link passes if applicable\n\n**buildModuleOptimizationPipeline (lines 1477-1651)**:\nThis is the O2/O3 optimization pipeline that includes:\n1. Partial inlining (line 1486)\n2. Reverse post-order function attribute inference (line 1503)\n3. PGO instrumentation passes (lines 1509-1517)\n4. Recompute GlobalsAA (line 1528)\n5. Function-level optimization PM (OptimizePM):\n   - Loop optimization: LoopRotatePass, LoopDeletionPass, LoopInterchangePass (lines 1580-1590)\n   - Loop distribution (line 1604)\n   - Vector passes (line 1610)\n   - LoopSinkPass (line 1618)\n   - InstSimplifyPass (line 1621)\n   - DivRemPairsPass (line 1626)\n   - TailCallElimPass (line 1630)\n   - SimplifyCFGPass (line 1635)\n6. Module-level optimization via ModuleToFunctionPassAdaptor (line 1642)\n7. AllocTokenPass if non-LTO (line 1648)\n\n### Pass Registry Definitions (llvm/lib/Passes/PassRegistry.def)\nMacro-based registry that defines all available passes:\n- MODULE_ANALYSIS: Module-level analyses (CallGraph, DXILMetadata, etc.)\n- MODULE_PASS: Module passes (AlwaysInliner, Annotation2Metadata, Attributor, etc.)\n- CGSCC_PASS: Call graph SCC passes\n- FUNCTION_PASS: Function passes\n- LOOP_PASS: Loop passes\n- Each pass definition allows the pass to be constructed via PassBuilder and named in command-line interfaces\n\n### Pass Execution Flow (llvm/lib/IR/PassManager.cpp)\nWhen PassManager::run() is called:\n1. For each registered pass (line 225 - Passes vector)\n2. Retrieves PreservedAnalyses from previous pass\n3. Calls pass's run() method with IR unit and AnalysisManager\n4. AnalysisManager invalidates analyses based on PreservedAnalyses (lines 31-94 show invalidation logic)\n5. ModuleToFunctionPassAdaptor (lines 107-148) adapts module passes to run on functions:\n   - Gets FunctionAnalysisManager from module analysis manager\n   - Runs function pass on each function\n   - Handles analysis invalidation per-function\n\n### Key Design Patterns\n\n1. **Concept-Based Polymorphism**: PassManager uses type erasure through PassConcept and PassModel to support any pass type without virtual inheritance\n\n2. **Analysis Management**: Passes declare required/preserved analyses via PreservedAnalyses. Analysis results are cached and invalidated based on pass requirements.\n\n3. **Extension Points**: PassBuilder provides callbacks for inserting custom passes:\n   - registerOptimizerEarlyEPCallback() - early optimizer extension\n   - registerOptimizerLastEPCallback() - late optimizer extension\n   - registerPeepholeEPCallback() - peephole extension\n   - registerVectorizerStartEPCallback(), registerVectorizerEndEPCallback()\n\n4. **Adaptor Pattern**: Uses ModuleToFunctionPassAdaptor and similar to run lower-level passes within higher-level pass managers\n\n5. **Hierarchical Execution**: Modules → Functions → Loops → Instructions with appropriate analysis managers at each level"
